Name: Teak Tree
Description: Premium timber tree used in furniture and shipbuilding
Pros: Strong durable wood, long lifespan, high commercial value

Name: Bael Tree
Description: Sacred medicinal tree with religious and cultural significance

Name: Neem Tree
Description: Highly medicinal tree known for pest-repellent and healing properties
Pros: Purifies air, strong antibacterial/antifungal, natural pesticide

Name: Karanj Tree
Description: Oil-producing tree used for biodiesel and traditional medicine
Pros: Produces non-edible oil for fuel, provides shade, nitrogen-fixing

Name: Coconut Tree
Description: Tropical palm tree producing nutritious coconuts
Pros: Produces versatile fruit and oil, provides tropical aesthetic

Name: Peach Tree
Description: Deciduous fruit tree producing sweet stone fruits
Pros: Produces delicious fruit, beautiful spring blossoms
Cons: Sensitive to frost and extreme heat

Name: Pothos Plant
Description: Trailing indoor houseplant with heart-shaped leaves
Pros: Low maintenance, air-purifying, grows in low light

Name: Adenium
Description: Desert rose with vibrant colorful flowers
Pros: Beautiful ornamental flowers, drought tolerant, minimal care

Name: Rhaphidophora
Description: Mini monstera with intricate leaf patterns
Pros: Compact size, fast growing, trendy houseplant
